Your Inner Child Is Surprised
You see many things through the eyes of a child. Meaning, you're rarely cynical or jaded. You cherish all of the details in life. Easily fascinated, you enjoy experiencing new things.
How Is Your Inner Child?

Your Career Type: Realistic
You are practical and mechanical. Your talents lie in working with tools, mechanical or electrical drawings, machines, or animals. You would make an excellent: Carpenter - Diesel Mechanic - Electrician Farmer - Fire Fighter - Flight Engineer Forester - Locksmith - Locomotive Engineer Pilot - Police Officer - Truck Driver The worst career options for your are social careers, like social worker or teacher.
What's Your Ideal Career?

You Are 50% Weird
Normal enough to know that you're weird... But too damn weird to do anything about it!
How Weird Are You?

The Keys to Your Heart
You are attracted to those who are unbridled, untrammeled, and free. In love, you feel the most alive when your partner is patient and never willing to give up on you. You'd like to your lover to think you are stylish and alluring. You would be forced to break up with someone who was emotional, moody, and difficult to please. Your ideal relationship is open. Both of you can talk about everything... no secrets. Your risk of cheating is 100%. You are not suited for a monogamous relationship. You think of marriage as something precious. You'll treasure marriage and treat it as sacred. In this moment, you think of love as commitment. Love only works when both people are totally devoted.
What Are The Keys To Your Heart?

Some people are so mean and miserable.  Others just don't want to help you.  Then people just don't know SHIT!!!!  AND NOW THERE'S A FUCKING TUBA IN MY ROOM!!!!!  Not exactly my best morning.  Especially since I almost cried.

It turns out that i'm terrible at abstracts.  Out of four i do believe one of them was acceptable.  Fuck WORLD POETRY!!!!  Then I went to get a euphonium and they were out of them.  Figures.  Then i miss lunch because i wanted to take a nap.  Then i sit through band without an instrument again.  I love doing that.  Then the day gets better.  I go to dinner with marc and steve and have a good time.  Then racquetball was amazingly fun with marc.  Then Richa tells me that mom called and that i should call her right back.  "How's everything going with college?"  "Oh i think i'm doing ok except that i'm terrible at analyzing poems."  "Andrea, Bobby died this morning......."  Crash, the ceiling falls right on my head.  My favorite uncle is now gone and again i didn't get to say my last goodbyes to someone that i really cared for.  The greatest ending to a half shit filled day.  Going home this weekend for a funeral.  




RIP
Bobby Mead 
6/17/39-9/1/05 (67yrs old)

It starts off ok then i don't know how it progressed so quickly into what it became!
Oh well, I was laughing my ass off through the whole thing!

My first week of college was not as bad as i thought it would be.  I seriously thought i would cry when my parents left.  Instead i prompted them to leave.  I was proud of myself for that.  In my classes there hasn't really been a lot for me to do.  I just haven't learned to manage my time yet.  If i can get that down I'll be doing great.  I did my first load of laundry and none of my underwear turned pink.  A total success in my eyes.  I have discovered racquetball and i do believe i am terrible at it but i do like it a lot.  My roommate is really nice and strangely karma didn't bite me in the ass or at least not in this situation.  There have been others but i think i'll leave them alone because it seems that every time that i open my mouth i get myself into trouble.  I really hope that if i gain anything from college it will be some freaking social grace.  I am entirely tired of sticking my foot in my mouth so often that the taste of rubber stays with me for a week later.  
    Anyways i've joined All College Band (ACB) but lucky me i still don't have an instrument yet.  Figure that.  I would like to sign up for an intramural sport or a club of some sort i just don't know which yet.  I really enjoyed having Teeny stay the night with me.  I just wish she could have gone to some of my classes.  I didn't even think to ask if she could sit in the non-full ones.  I guess that can wait for another time.  
    Today i got up at 8:30 and I had a niner.  Not exactly a great way to start out the day.  I then proceeded to get the milk out for the cereal that i wanted the night before.  Off comes the top and i get a whiff of a cheesey smell.  I think to myself that doesn't smell right but maybe it's just because i'm tired and i don't know what the hell i was thinking.  Anyway, i take a drink of it and i was correct in thinking that it was bad because IT WAS!!!!!  I am dumber than a box of rocks at times and that was one of them.  After intro to performing arts and calc. i went to lunch with Keri.  It was packed in Erie and all those people just always seem to be standing right in the way.  But the thing is they are just talking and doing exactly that.  BLOCKING THE WAY!  I'm not sure why the don't just sit down but they don't and i swear i almost started twitching.  Then I went to art history and almost fell asleep.  I had to take a nap afterward to be sure that i didn't fall asleep while walking.  After waking up at like 5:30 from falling asleep at two, I got some of my world poetry done.  Then I went to dinner by myself and ended up sitting with a couple of people that i had met when I stayed up for the host program.  They actually recognized me and shocked the crap out of me in doing so.  It was a little awkward but that's ok, they were very nice.  
   Basically that is all for now.  I'm not exactly the hot spot for excitement.

You know what, I totally wasn't thinking when i wrote the first entry.  You have every right to be pissed at me and hate my guts!!  If you would have done that to me I would have been pissed.  Again, I am sorry more than I ever have been in my life.

How do I make any of this better?  Well by saying that I am a biased BASTARD!!!  I am encredibly SORRY that I said that.  I am biased.  It's just that every blond that I have encountered at my school was preppy.  I'm not saying that all blonds are like that.  I'm just nervous and I am terrible with words and people for that matter.  I really don't try to judge people at a first glance and I'm usually good at that.  When I talked to you, you sounded like a very nice girl and I find it very respectable that you work for everything.  Let me say again that I am SO SORRY and hope that my shear stupidity won't murder a friendship that we could probably have!!!!!

Today, was interesting.  At work I was laughing at everything.  Every single mistake, I would laugh my ass off.  These people came in and this boy had a kid on his shoulders.  The only thing I could think of was "Look, that boy has a monkey on his shoulder!"  The little kid was clinging to the boys shoulders and I was being kinda mean about the situation in my head.  These people were on welfare and all I could think of was the monkey comment.  I was laughing so hard I couldn't stand it.  I'm so mean.  Thank God that day is over.  
Other than that my day was boring as hell!  Yeah!!

Two months later anthat d I still don't have all my thank you cards done!  Ah shit.  Oh well.  Procrastination at its best!

Going to Texas Hot with the boys was very fun.  I thoroughly enoyed when steve called himself partially retarded.  I don't agree but it was still hillarious.  I didn't make a fool of myself because, thank god I had a meal where I could eat it with a fork.  Yeah for forks.  Well I'm not sure I enjoy forks when I get stabbed with them or when people try to take them away from me because I try to stab them with them.  Anyways, I had a really good time eating out and watching the movies.  Even Punch Drunk Love which was a tad bit confusing.

Today at work was a lot better.  Nobody pissed me off and I didn't feel like strangling anyone today.  Therefore, it was a good day.  Plus, I was able to keep the perma-grin in place today.  That alone shows that it was a good day.  Oh well.  I have to work tomorrow and we'll see what goes down.  

I saw a picture of my roommate today.  And guess what I saw.  Probably what I least wanted to see.  A preppy looking blond.  Oh joy!  I do believe that I am prejudice against blonds.  I tend to stereotype them as stuck up and high maintenance.  Hmmm, I never realized that I have no blond friends.  What a realization.  Well, I guess we'll see how it goes.  Only time will tell.
